OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,432,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F431A1780902267
OL,3,CBath adventurer becomes first British
OL,4,Cwoman to cross Atlantic by balloon
OL,6,FThe crew were travelling in an open
OL,7,Fbasket, exposed to the elements
OL,8,Fthroughout the crossing.
OL,10,FOnce clear of Newfoundland, the only
OL,11,Falternative landing place would have
OL,12,Fbeen the open ocean.
OL,14,FThe pilots had to fly the balloon at
OL,15,Fdiffering altitudes in order to
OL,16,Fachieve the correct trajectory.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
